no.motif.types

Interface Elements<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the contained objects.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Appendable<T>, Existance<T>, Filterable<T>, Iterable<T>, Mappable<T>, Prependable<T>, Reducible<T>, YieldsJavaCollection<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PreparedIterable

    public interface Elements<T>
extends Mappable<T>, Filterable<T>, Appendable<T>, Prependable<T>, YieldsJavaCollection<T>, Existance<T>, Iterable<T>, Reducible<T>
    This is the main type of Motif's collection API and encompasses all the operations available to manipulate and query the the contained elements, as well as converting back to Java Collection Framework collections.
